    <p>• Spring­bok Aphiwe Dyan­tyi has been banned for four years af­ter tak­ing three il­le­gal sub­stances, the South African In­sti­tute for Drug-free Sport con­firmed yesterday.</p>
    <p>The 26-year-old winger, who plays for the Lions in Su­per Rugby, tested pos­i­tive for metan­dienone, methyl­testos­terone and LGD-4033 while at­tend­ing a Spring­boks camp last year and his B sam­ple also came back pos­i­tive.</p>


